		<!-- message -->
		<div><div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				<div>Originally Posted by <strong>Flintnilf</strong></div>
				<div style="font-style:italic"> Why should rogues be better than wizards in pure burst? why should wizards be better than rogues in pure burst? Both are damage classes, why can't it be relatively even (which i think it is right now)</div>
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div> The logical progression of your question is, &quot;Why should any specific offensive class be the best at burst damage?&quot;  After all, there are many more &quot;damage classes&quot; than the two you mention.  Should they all perform equally, diminishing game mechanics such as range vs melee and mana as mere flavor?  If you plotted damage vs time on a graph, should they all look similar?  There is no right or wrong answer.<br />
<br />
Personally, I would answer no.  I think casters, whose offensive capabilities are a direct function of a finite resource - mana - should favor short term dps.  If you are based on mana, you should contribute &quot;premier&quot; burst damage and &quot;acceptable but below melee&quot; sustained dps.  Conversely, melee should offer &quot;good&quot; burst damage and &quot;good&quot; sustained damage.<br />
<br />
There's an entire spectrum of variations on this theme but it, in my humble opinion, is a solid base.  It's riddled with its own issues, however.  A group is primarily concerned with sustained dps so casters need &quot;something else&quot; to make them desirable.  Conversely, a raid is primarily concerned with burst dps, so melee also need something else to make them desirable.<br />
<br />
But that's just &quot;The Vision by Sinari - Quick, dirty and filled with holes.&quot;</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
